			    STPJS 227</div>
  <p class="cont">being your associates. Females, if they are pure<span class="footRef">1</span> and innocent, can come in the presence of God;<span class="footRef">2</span>
  for what is more pleasing to God<span class="footRef">3</span> than innocence; you must be innocent,<span class="footRef">4</span> or you cannot come up
  before God; if we would come before God, we must keep ourselves pure, as He is pure.<span class="footRef">5</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Devil&rsquo;s Power to Deceive</div>
  <p class="std">The devil has great power to deceive;<span class="footRef">6</span> he will so transform things as to make one gape at those
  who are doing the will of God.<span class="footRef">7</span> You need not be teasing your husbands because of their deeds, but
  let the weight of your innocence, kindness and affection be felt, which is more mighty than a
  millstone hung about the neck;<span class="footRef">8</span> not war, not jangle, not contradiction, or dispute, but meekness,
  love, purity&mdash;these are the things that should magnify you in the eyes of all good men. Achan [see
  Joshua 7]<span class="footRef">9</span> must be brought to light, iniquity must be purged<span class="footRef">10</span> out from the midst of the Saints; then
  the veil will be rent,<span class="footRef">11</span> and the blessings of heaven<span class="footRef">12</span> will flow down&mdash;they will roll down like the
  Mississippi river.<span class="footRef">13</span></p>
  <p class="std">If this Society listen to the counsel<span class="footRef">14</span> of the Almighty, through the heads of the Church,<span class="footRef">15</span> they
  shall have power to command queens in their midst.<span class="footRef">16</span></p>
  <p class="std">I now deliver it as a prophecy, if the inhabitants of this state, with the people of the surrounding
  country, will turn unto the Lord with all their hearts,<span class="footRef">17</span> ten years will not roll around before the kings
  and queens of the earth will come unto Zion,<span class="footRef">18</span> and pay their respects to the leaders of this people;
  they shall come with their millions, and shall contribute of their abundance for the relief of the poor,
  and the building up and beautifying of Zion.</p>
  <p class="std">After this instruction, you will be responsible for your own sins;<span class="footRef">19</span> it is a desirable honor that
  you should so walk before our heavenly Father<span class="footRef">20</span> as to save yourselves;<span class="footRef">21</span> we are all responsible to
  God for the manner we improve the light<span class="footRef">22</span> and wisdom given by our Lord to enable us to save
  ourselves.</p>
  <div class="topic">Beware of Self-Righteousness</div>
  <p class="std">President Smith continued reading from the above-mentioned chapter,<span class="footRef">23</span> and to give instructions
  respecting the order of God,<span class="footRef">24</span> as established in the Church, saying everyone should aspire only to
  magnify his own office and calling.<span class="footRef">25</span></p>
